nit: Was this change caused by clang-format? Did something else changed except formatting and BMCWEB_LOG?

Yes, clang-formats formatting of lambdas is very fickle, which is why we're trying to move away from lambdas for non trivial routines, which any help you wanted to give would be greatly appreciated.  Yes, the only thing that changed was the length of some of the BMCWEB_LOG strings.
Done.  Fixed issue in script with handling of single quotes.  Good catch!

While you're probably right, this is the way it was before.  If we wanted to walk through and fix all these, we should do it in another commit.  I would like to keep this commit limited to things that the automated script can handle.  These things should be easy to grep for.
See above.  This was this way before, I'd rather not fix it in this commit, which is largely automated.
How did you choose fmt? Did you consider anything else?

It's what most of the rest of the project is using, is already available, and is pretty much the standard goto choice for c++ log formatting.  I also considered printf/varargs forwarding, but that has its own issues.

Open to other ideas though.

One thing that I considered after I wrote this was to use spdlog directly instead of our own logging class.  I'm not sure the binary-size consequences of that, but it might be worth it to not have our own logging class.  With that said, the logging class is a trivial amount of code, so even if we went with that approach, I'd probably still do it in two steps.

I am good with fmt. 
I think just add a bit of this to the commit msg. I am good moving forward with this commit.
In general, I would support using fmt, and dropping logging

sounds good,
fmt is very standard
You could mention logPtr, oh well.

And i assuming using a logging level like Error or Warning still works?
https://github.com/openbmc/bmcweb/commit/662aa6e361f8705cfd91261080324ff0e74778e4

Yep, this patchset predated that work to make the levels configurable.  I updated it to add support for it (which was largely just changing a variable around.)

Thank you for catching that.  I had forgotten that logging was configurable now.
might be good to add to the tested msg.
Thanks for the review John.  I do appreciate it.

Note to reviewer, SSL_CTX_set_ecdh_auto is now deprecated, and the gcc analyzer now realizes this is dead code that will never execute.  I removed it for now to get the compiler to not complain, and will fix it in the next patch.

This is intended to go away, maybe end of 2023? 
Could you add that here? 2 reasons: 1) we remember to remove this and gives a date. 2) gives anyone running it a heads up.

nit:

Wouldn't this be better done like this?

```
[ERROR event_service_manager.hpp:1301] 
```

I see two changes in your above:

1. Changing Error to ERROR.  The old output had Error, so lets keep it the same, and if we want to change it, do it in another patchset.
2. removing the relative folder structure.  I believe having the full path helps users to find the right file quickly.  Why would we omit the folder?

Not a strong opinion.

- Capital words may be more visible?  
- I think most of file names are already unique, and they are primarily for the developers. 
- Also, short prefix in the log by putting only base file name.
IMO Full path fits in with other logging. I also agree with full path helps users to find the right file quickly.
BTW, I'm open to discussion on this, I just didn't want to hold up this very-merge-conflict-causing patch while we debated this.
nit: Do we need two spaces here?
This commit faithfully puts forward what was there before, which included two spaces.  It's unlikely that was on purpose, but lets fix that in another patch.
